SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 995
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR GREGORY (15).
5487S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal sections 57.450 and 57.452, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof two new sections relating
to the sheriff of the city of St. Louis.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Sections 57.450 and 57.452, RSMo, are repealed
2 and two new sections enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as
3 sections 57.450 and 57.452, to read as follows:
1 57.450. 1. The sheriff of the City of St. Louis shall
2 be appointed by a majority of the circuit judges and
3 associate circuit judges of the twenty-second judicial
4 circuit, en banc. The sheriff in such circuit shall be
5 removable for cause by a majority of the circuit judges and
6 associate circuit judges of such circuit, en banc, in
7 accordance with the Missouri supreme court administrative
8 rules governing court personnel. Such sheriff shall meet
9 the same qualifications and requirements specified in
10 subsection 1 of section 57.010 for elected sheriffs. The
11 elected sheriff holding office on August 28, 2026, shall
12 continue to hold such office for the remainder of his or her
13 term. Notwithstanding the provisions of section 57.080 to
14 the contrary, should a vacancy occur from any cause in the
15 office of sheriff of the City of St. Louis during the
16 remainder of the current term of the elected sheriff, the
17 vacancy shall be filled by appointment by a majority of the
