18 circuit judges and associate circuit judges of the twenty-
19 second judicial circuit, en banc.
20 2. All general laws relating and applicable to the
21 sheriffs of the several counties of this state shall apply
22 to the same officer in the City of St. Louis, except that
23 the sheriff of the City of St. Louis shall not enforce the
24 general criminal laws of the state of Missouri unless such
25 enforcement shall be incidental to the duties customarily
26 performed by the sheriff of the City of St. Louis. The
27 sheriff and sworn deputies of the office of sheriff of the
28 City of St. Louis may be eligible for training and licensure
29 by the peace officer standards and training commission under
30 chapter 590, and such office shall be considered a law
31 enforcement agency with the sheriff and sworn deputies
32 considered law enforcement officers. All acts and parts of
33 acts providing for any legal process to be directed to any
34 sheriff of any county shall be so construed as to mean the
35 sheriff of the City of St. Louis as if such officer were
36 specifically named in such act.
1 57.452. The provisions of section 590.180 shall not
2 apply to any [elected or appointed] sheriff of a city not
3 within a county.
